description:
&lt;p&gt;Service/Ward/Department Summary:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen within Adult Mental Health for a Receptionist / Clerical Officer to join our team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Role Summary:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To provide an efficient, responsive and quality reception service to support the medical staff with the Adult Age Psychiatric Outpatient Departments as well as the provision of general clerical support, ensuring high standards are maintained at all times and that work is produced efficiently, in accordance with Trust policies and procedures.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Key Responsibilities of the Post:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Provide a comprehensive reception service, dealing with clients and professionals attending for appointments or enquiries in a sensitive and professional manner.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dealing with telephone enquiries and taking accurate messages from professionals and clients/carers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Promoting good customer care and anti-discriminatory practice.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Entering data on Paris IT systems.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;General admin duties.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Maintaining confidentiality of client/carer information.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Filing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Key Requirements of the Person Specification:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Good standard of education including GCSE English and Maths (or equivalent).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Paris trained.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Previous experience of working in a Reception environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Good communication and interpersonal skills both face to face and over the telephone.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Able to handle confidential information with tact and diplomacy&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameAlison HickingbothamJob titleOutpatient ManagerTelephone number0161 716 1025&lt;/p&gt;
